This file is not a history of bugs but a list line by line of known
issues in this release.  If you wish to comment on any of them or have
patches to fix any of them please email Overlord@DayboLogic.co.uk
(maintainer).

----------------------------------------------------------------------
File/line reports in C++ report owner as dpccap.cpp not the true owner.
Truely portable --maxport --enable-threads mutlithreaded builds on UNIX allow callbacks to deadlock the thread.  I am seeing this as just an unfortunate thing we have to accept and use the NP POSIX extensions for recursive mutexes if possible.  Unless you have a better idea?
Library can lock the big lock after it destroyed it during shutdown.
